how to make paneer manchurian dry recipe
paneer manchurian is a spicy manchurian made from paneer cottage cheese is
the most delicious and best indo chinese dish it is one of the most delicious
paneer dishes served as a starters or evening snack paneer manchurian is
liked by all and is very much popular at parties paneer manchurian is an easy
indo chinese paneer dish which is the most liked party food you can easily
make delicious paneer manchurian at home by following this detailed recipe
paneer cottage cheese 250 grams refined flour maida 2 tablespoon
cornflour 4 tablespoon garlic paste 1/2 teaspoon ginger paste 1/2
teaspoon salt 1/4 teaspoon or as per taste chaat masala 1/2 teaspoon ghee
or cooking oil for deep fry water 1/4 cup
small diced capsicum 1/4 cup small diced onion 1 medium grated ginger
1/2 teaspoon grated garlic 1/2 teaspoon green chilli finely chopped 2
spring onion finely chopped 2 tablespoon ghee or cooking oil 2 tablespoon
soy sauce 1 tablespoon green chilli sauce 1/2 tablespoon tomato ketchup 2
tablespoon black salt 1/2 teaspoon chaat masala to sprinkle
cut the cottage cheese paneer into small size cube or to your liking
add refined flour maida corn flour ginger paste garlic paste salt and chaat masala to a bowl and mix well gradually add water and make a thick batter make sure there are no lumps in the batter
make sure the batter should not be too thick and not too thin add paneer to this batter and let it rest for about 20 minutes to marinate
heat the ghee in a wok on medium heat when the ghee is sufficiently hot add marinated paneer cubes in a solution of 3 4 paneer cubes and fry over medium heat them until they turn golden brown
transfer the fried paneer to a plate on kitchen tissue paper to absorb excess oil
heat 2 tablespoon of ghee or cooking oil in a pan when the ghee gets hot add ginger paste garlic paste and fry it for about 30 seconds
now add diced capsicum onion and chopped green chillies and fry it for about 3 4 minutes while stirring occasionally
add chili sauce soy sauce tomato ketchup and salt and mix well add the fried paneer and spring onion and mix well while tossing all in the pan cook it on high flame for about 2 3 minutes
transfer the paneer manchurian to the serving bowl and garnish it with spring onion and sprinkle some chaat masala over it paneer manchurian is ready enjoy hot paneer manchurian as a snack
